      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Mayor Moore today received a\nletter from Pres. Howard Elliott,\nof the Northern Pacific. in which\nhe practically repeats the contents\nof a former letter from Counsel\nCannon of the road. which was to\nthe effect that the Northern Pacl-\nfic would not give consideration to\nCity Engineer Ralston's plan for a\ncommon right Of way through the\ncity and tunnel through Cannon\nhill.\n\n\n1t is expected that the mayor\nwill call the municipal railway\ncommission together next week\nand place before 1t all the replies\nreceived from railroad men, so a\nreport may be made to the coun-\nGil.\n\n\nThe N. p. has rejected the tun-\nmel project so often now that 1t is\ncoming to be regarded in the light\nof a girl turning down proposal\nIn order to make a marriage more\ncertain."
    }
  ]
